Diagram 2 (Demonstration)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Continuing from the previous diagram, even if black connects at 1, it is a good move for white to hane at 2 and the white \'a1\'e2 stone is connected. This leaves black with no way to live.
\par
\par Instead of black 1, if black connects at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , white still plays at 2 and captures black.
\par Instead of black 1, if black plays at \b\f1 B\b0\f0 , white plays \b\f1 A\b0\f0  and that's it.
\par }
